  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened but not coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion softens, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>arborio rice </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains of rice in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong>, with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, carefully peel and discard the skin then flake the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>salmon</strong> gently with a fork and keep warm</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> into quarters</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>mangetout</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped chives</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice </strong>to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong></p><p>Grind everything until you're left with a green oil – this is your <strong>chive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is almost cooked, add the<strong> halved mangetout</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further</p><p>Remove the<strong> cooked risotto</strong> from the heat and stir through the<strong> grated cheese </strong>with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon quarter[s]</strong> and season very generously with <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>mangetout risotto</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if your risotto is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-and-mangetout-risotto-with-chive-oil/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> remaining lemon quarter[s] </strong>in <strong>half</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>mangetout</strong> <strong>risotto</strong>, topped with the <strong>flaked salmon</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>chive oil</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
